\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\f0\fs29 Define "third-party control".\par
}

FillIn.Answer:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1033{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Microsoft Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\f0\fs29 A control that is not created or maintained by the project team. Developers use these controls to shorten the schedule length and reduce risk. A thirdparty control can be something embedded in the Visual Studio Toolbox and used on a Web form, or it could be an entire application such as Microsoft BizTalk Server or Commerce Server.\par
}

